refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
final public stringMongoDB\Driver\Server::getLatency
Returns the latency of this server (i.e. the client's measured round trip time of a hello command).

  &reftitle.examples;

   MongoDB\Driver\Server::getLatency example


<?php

$manager = new MongoDB\Driver\Manager("mongodb://localhost:27017/");

$rp = new MongoDB\Driver\ReadPreference(MongoDB\Driver\ReadPreference::RP_PRIMARY);
$server = $manager->selectServer($rp);

var_dump($server->getLatency());

?>


   &example.outputs.similar;


int(592)

